<div id="entry-43096" class="entry-asset asset hentry">
  <div class="asset-header">
    <h2>Knitting instructions</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="asset-content entry-content">
    
      <div class="asset-body">
        <img src="http://blog.makezine.com/caston-1.jpg" height="500" width="400" border="0" hspace="4" vspace="4" alt="Caston-1" />
<br />Flickr user tofuttibreak scanned in an old out of print knitting booklet that has more clear and concise knitting instructions.  The simple illustrations are great.  It's a handy reference to bookmark when you just can't remember how to cast on or do a slip stitch.  [ <a href="http://www.diyhappy.com/learn-to-knit/">via</a> ] <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/tofuttibreak/sets/72157594221964508/">Link.</a>
<br /><br /><br />
      </div>
    
    
  </div>
 <br clear="all" />
  <div class="asset-footer">
    <div class="asset-meta">
